SUMMARY:2026 Goldschmidt Data Fellowship – Washington\, D.C.
DESCRIPTION:The 2026 Goldschmidt Fellowship data immersion workshop that will take place Sunday\, April 12 – Thursday\, April 16 in Washington\, D.C. Fellows will visit agencies in the District of Columbia/Maryland area\, as well as have training and other events in downtown Washington. \nThis is an all-access program for journalists to learn from experts and government professionals who gather and analyze the nation’s economic data. \nThe workshop is in its twelfth year and is funded annually by a grant from the Illinois-based Walter and Karla Goldschmidt Foundation. \nIt is coordinated by Marty Steffens\, SABEW chair at the University of Missouri School of Journalism and Kevin Hall\, former SABEW president and managing editor/Americas\, OCCRP. \nIf you have any questions about the program\, email logistics@sabew.org.
URL:https://sabew.org/event/2026-goldschmidt-data-fellowship-washington-d-c/
