UID:407727bca8389c851452ffbf89cd1770@pen.org
DESCRIPTION:Cost: 175\nJoin us for an intimate dinner with\nIra Madison II
 I\nin celebration of his national bestseller\nPure Innocent Fun.\nThis eve
 ning is generously hosted by Linzee Troubh. Books will be available for al
 l attendees.\nIn this nostalgic and raucous collection of sixteen original
  essays\, Ira Madison III—critic\, television writer\, and host of the b
 eloved\nKeep It\npodcast—combines memoir and criticism to offer a brand-
 new pop-culture manifesto.\n“This is the most fun I’ve had reading all
  year. Like Chuck Klosterman before him\, Ira Madison III takes seriously 
 and analyzes the pop culture detritus that took up hours of our lives.”
 —Lin-Manuel Miranda\nYou can recall the first TV show\, movie\, book\, o
 r song that made you feel understood—that shaped how you live\, what you
  love\, and whom you would become. It gave you an entire worldview. For Ir
 a Madison\, that book was Chuck Klosterman’s\nSex\, Drugs\, and Cocoa Pu
 ffs\,\nwhich cemented the idea that pop culture could be a rigorous subjec
 t—and that\, for better or worse\, it shapes all of us.\nIn\nPure Innoce
 nt Fun\n\, Madison explores the key cultural moments that inspired his car
 eer as a critic and guided his coming of age as a Black gay man in Milwauk
 ee. In this hilarious\, full-throttle trip through the ’90s and 2000s\, 
 he recounts learning about sex from\nBuffy the Vampire Slayer\;\nfacing th
 e most heartbreaking election of his youth (not George W. Bush’s win\, b
 ut Jennifer Hudson losing American Idol)\; and how never getting his drive
 r’s license in high school made him just like Cher Horowitz in\nClueless
 \n: “a virgin who can’t drive.”\nBrimming with a profound love for a
  bygone culture and alternating between irreverence and heartfelt insight\
 ,\nPure Innocent Fun\n\, like all the best products of pop culture\, will 
 leave you entertained and surprisingly enlightened.\nAbout\nIra Madison II
 I\nIra Madison III\nis the host of Crooked Media’s pop culture podcast\n
 Keep It\n. His television credits include\nUncoupled\, Q-Force\n\,\nNikki 
 Fre$h\n\, and\nSo Help Me Todd\n. He has wri
LOCATION:New York
URL:https://pen.org/event/authors-evening-ira-madison-iii/
X-SOURCE:PEN America
END:VEVENT
